# Odin Recipes Project 🍛

## Description

This repository contains my solution for The Odin Project's recipe website assignment. The project demonstrates basic HTML skills through the creation of a simple recipe website, featuring a delicious Chicken Curry recipe along with structured content and proper HTML semantics.

## Project Structure

```
odin-recipes/
│
├── README
├── index.html
├── images/
│   └── chicken-curry.png
└── recipes/
    └── chicken-curry.html
```

## Features

- Homepage with recipe navigation
- Detailed chicken curry recipe page including:
  - High-quality recipe image
  - List of ingredients
  - Step-by-step cooking instructions
  - Clear recipe description

## Technologies Used

- HTML5
- Git/GitHub for version control

## Skills Demonstrated

- HTML boilerplate creation
- Working with headings and paragraphs
- Creating ordered and unordered lists
- Adding images with proper file organization
- Creating links between pages
- Basic file structure organization
- Git workflow and commits

## Project Requirements Met

✅ Created main index page
✅ Set up proper directory structure
✅ Included recipe images in separate directory
✅ Listed ingredients
✅ Provided step-by-step instructions
✅ Implemented proper HTML structure
✅ Added navigation between pages

## Future Improvements

- Add CSS styling
- Include more recipes
- Add nutritional information
- Implement responsive design
- Add cooking time and difficulty level
- Include search functionality

## Getting Started

1. Clone the repository:
   ```bash
   git clone https://github.com/sadiqhassan41/odin-recipes.git
   ```
2. Open `index.html` in your web browser

